# GR-02 NON-AUTHORITATIVE MARKER (Founder D-184 §B): the SECURITY directives below
# are NOT applied to live SSR responses. In this output:'server' + @astrojs/cloudflare
# deployment the SSR Worker serves responses and does NOT apply this static _headers
# file (same dead-file class as the retired public/_redirects — see astro.config.mjs).
# The AUTHORITATIVE live security-header mechanism is the SSR middleware response path
# (src/middleware.ts, applyTierASecurityHeaders). This file is retained ONLY for its
# (unverified) 103 Early-Hints Link preloads + per-path Cache-Control; do not rely on
# its X-Frame-Options/Referrer-Policy/CSP/COOP/COEP/CORP/HSTS lines for live coverage.
# V21.10.1: Definitive Security & Caching Enclave (Ratified)
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

# V25.1: Edge Cache — browser no-cache but Cloudflare caches 1h (Atomic Purge guarantees freshness)
/model/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate, s-maxage=3600
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

# V25.1: 103 Early Hints — preload VFS only on search-heavy pages (not global — 6.3MB kills LCP)
/
  Link: </assets/sqlite/wa-sqlite-async.wasm>; rel=preload; as=fetch; crossorigin
  Link: </api/vfs-proxy/hot-shard.bin>; rel=preload; as=fetch; crossorigin
/search
  Link: </assets/sqlite/wa-sqlite-async.wasm>; rel=preload; as=fetch; crossorigin
  Link: </api/vfs-proxy/hot-shard.bin>; rel=preload; as=fetch; crossorigin
/models
  Link: </assets/sqlite/wa-sqlite-async.wasm>; rel=preload; as=fetch; crossorigin
